oai_dc:dc.dc:title: WAVE-INDUCED SHOCK PRESSURES UNDER REAL SEA STATE CONDITIONS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Grune, Joachim
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: shock pressure
sea state
wave induced shock pressure
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This paper deals with a study on shock pressures, which occur on sloping seadykes and revetments due to breaking waves. Results from field measurements are presented with respect to peak pressure values as well as to characteristics of pressure-time histories.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 21 (1988): Proceedings of 21st Conference on Coastal Engineering, Torremolinos, Spain, 1988.; 173
